# S02-T01: Types

## Objective
Define all shared TypeScript types for the game in `src/game/types.ts`.
This file is the single source of truth — no inline types anywhere else.

## Acceptance Criteria
- All types exported from `src/game/types.ts`.
- No `any`, no `object` — strict typing throughout.
- TypeScript compiles without errors.

## Steps
1. Create `src/game/types.ts`.
2. Define `GamePhase`: `'idle' | 'playing' | 'result' | 'gameover'`.
3. Define `Note`: `{ midi: number; name: string; accidental: boolean }`.
4. Define `Question`: `{ target: Note; options: readonly Note[] }`.
5. Define `AnswerResult`: `{ midi: number; correct: boolean; timestamp: number }`.
6. Define `LevelConfig`: `{ level: number; notePool: readonly number[]; timerMs: number; optionCount: number; label: string }`.
7. Define `GameState`: `{ phase: GamePhase; score: number; streak: number; best: number; level: number; question: Question | null; lastResult: AnswerResult | null }`.
8. `git commit -m "feat: game types"`.
